    Save and read R object from disk

    evaluate.and.save.Rd

    This function generates an R object if it does not exist, but reads the object from disk if it exists.

    Usage

    evaluate.and.save(object.path, object.constructor, should.print = TRUE, should.flush = FALSE);

    Arguments

    object.path

    The path for the R object

    object.constructor

    A function that returns the R object

    should.print

    A logical indicating whether to print disk activity

    should.flush

    A logical indicating whether to flush the object stored on disk

    Value

    R Object

    Author

    Nathaniel Schmitz
